commits.message: Adjusted version of package.json to match our current release

Updated tutorial-week-4.md

Added a simpler explanation of what pseudocode is and proof read for accuracy and coherence.

Merge pull request #17 from jeffworley/tutorial-week-4

tutorial-week-4.md -- Completed assignment for this branch.
Added parameters to next and prev functions to prevent going 'outside' the array of moves and cleaned up old code

Added link to view-helpers.js in cb-index.html, refactored main.js to account for our moves json, connected main.js to controllers.js, adjusted tests.js, fixed sass shortcut in package.json, added sass for chess pieces in main.scss and got the view to match the internal board except for a weird letter representation side effect
Added play functionality but haven't solved stopping it upon finish or paused
Attempted to lay groundwork for conditional clearInterval call in main.js
Corrected scss piece size unit and reopened all tests in tests.js to show a coherent suite of tests when I end up fixing them
Adjusted formatting

Merge pull request #5 from jeffworley/19--world-war-chess

19--world-war-chess -- Completed assignment for this branch
